   "source": [
    "Linear algebra\n",
    "==============\n",
    "\n",
    "Linear algebra is a fast and efficient means of solving silent substitution problems."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8ac84d51-9b64-4264-be18-122919fffa4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Basic example\n",
    "-------------"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "62f885b4-d9e9-4524-9741-a022aa8c49a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "************************************************************\n",
      "*************** Silent Substitution Problem ****************\n",
      "************************************************************\n",
      "Device: BCGAR (8-bit, linear)\n",
      "Observer: ColorimetricObserver(age=32, field_size=10)\n",
      "Ignoring: ['rh']\n",
      "Minimising: ['mc', 'lc', 'mel']\n",
      "Modulating: ['sc']\n",
      "Target contrast: [ 0.3]\n",
      "Background: [0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5]\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "The background settings are: [127, 127, 127, 127, 127]\n",
      "The modulation settings are: [245, 56, 129, 132, 83]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1300x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pysilsub.problems import SilentSubstitutionProblem as SSP\n",
    "\n",
    "# Instantiate the problem class for a 5-primary system\n",
    "ssp = SSP.from_package_data('BCGAR')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define problem\n",
    "ssp.ignore = ['rh']\n",
    "ssp.target = ['sc']\n",
    "ssp.silence = ['mc', 'lc', 'mel']\n",
    "ssp.background = [.5] * ssp.nprimaries\n",
    "ssp.target_contrast = .3\n",
    "ssp.print_problem()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find solution\n",
    "solution = ssp.linalg_solve()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot solution\n",
    "fig = ssp.plot_solution(solution)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show device settings\n",
    "print(f'The background settings are: {ssp.w2s(ssp.background)}')\n",
    "print(f'The modulation settings are: {ssp.w2s(solution)}')\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "Now, the unique scaling coefficients for the primaries $\\alpha_{sc} = [p_{0} \\ p_{1} \\ p_{2} \\ p_{3} \\ p_{4}]$ that must be added to the primary weights for the background $\\alpha_{bg}$ for a requested modulation $\\beta = [sc \\ mc \\ lc \\ rh \\ mel]$, are discovered as $\\alpha_{sc} = \\beta A^{-1}$."
   ]

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate inverse of A\n",
    "A1 = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    np.linalg.inv(A.values),\n",
    "    A.columns, \n",
    "    A.index)\n",
    "A1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "66681fd3-f1b8-4c08-9175-c6e55897ee6a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Primary\n",

     "execution_count": 6,

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Requested modulation for S-cones\n",
    "requested_contrast = .3\n",
    "\n",
    "# sc, mc, lc, rh, mel\n",
    "b = np.array([requested_contrast, 0., 0., 0., 0.])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scale requested contrasts to percentage of background units\n",
    "b = A.sum(axis=1).mul(b)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the scaling coefficients\n",
    "asc = A1.dot(b) / 2\n",
    "asc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aa2f6519-0362-4f31-9952-84e873eb1578",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Following on from above, $\\alpha_{mod} = \\alpha_{bg} + \\alpha_{sc}$."

     "output_type": "execute_result"

   "source": [

    "amod"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "da666463-a201-4417-b8e0-b4396a352601",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Obviously, these values need to be between zero and one for the solution to be valid, which in this case they are. As before, we can visualise the solution."

  },

    "# Show device settings\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d9692b66-303a-483c-8818-1ebf34664532",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Contrast modulations\n",
    "--------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "Multiprimary devices with good linearity, sufficient bit depth and rapid spectral switching capabilities may be used to present temporal modulations of photoreceptor-targeted contrast. Such stimuli have helped to shed light on how the pupil responds to input from different photoreceptors as a function of time (e.g., [Barrionuevo et al., 2016](https://jov.arvojournals.org/article.aspx?articleid=2565122); [Spitschan et al., 2014](https://www.pnas.org/doi/10.1073/pnas.1400942111)). \n",
    "\n",
    "To make contrast modulations, first define a stimulus profile with a sampling frequency in line with the switching capability of the stimulation device. In this case, its a 1 Hz sinusoid with 50 samples per cycle.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "8250cf7a-e57e-4450-af84-736170b3372d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f84517ba260>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from pysilsub import waves \n",
    "\n",
    "duration = 1  # s\n",
    "frequency = 1  # Hz\n",
    "sampling_frequency = 50  # Hz\n",
    "\n",
    "stimulus_profile = waves.make_stimulus_waveform(\n",
    "    frequency=frequency,\n",
    "    duration=duration,\n",
    "    sampling_frequency=sampling_frequency\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "time = np.linspace(0, duration, len(stimulus_profile))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(time, stimulus_profile)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "967d7d77-e8f3-4089-82e1-2e6d9ef1a83b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now, define a problem. Here we define the background spectrum as all primaries at half-max power so we can maximise bidirectional contrast. Then we say that we want to ignore rods, minimize contrast on M-cones, L-cones and melanopsin, and modulate the S-cones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "c94214c2-fbc5-4a5e-907e-544d8cb56a64",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "************************************************************\n",
      "*************** Silent Substitution Problem ****************\n",
      "************************************************************\n",
      "Device: STLAB_1 (binocular, left eye)\n",
      "Observer: ColorimetricObserver(age=32, field_size=10)\n",
      "Ignoring: ['rh']\n",
      "Minimising: ['mc', 'lc', 'mel']\n",
      "Modulating: ['sc']\n",
      "Target contrast: None\n",
      "Background: [0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5]\n",
      "\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Load some example data for a 10-primary system\n",
    "ssp = SSP.from_package_data('STLAB_1_York')\n",
    "\n",
    "ssp.background = [.5] * ssp.nprimaries\n",
    "ssp.ignore = ['rh']\n",
    "ssp.silence = ['mc', 'lc', 'mel']\n",
    "ssp.target = ['sc']\n",
    "ssp.print_problem()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1839fda0-795e-4bf7-b55c-8c99ee2fd31d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, choose a peak contrast value that is known to be in gamut and solve for each point in the stimulus profile. The algebraic approach is well suited here as it guarantees a linear uni-directional scaling of the primaries and is less computationally expensive than optimisation. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "64b3aec7-d53f-4a12-a6dc-bc4b0f2ede43",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 354x354 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "peak_contrast = .3  # Known to be within gamut\n",
    "solutions = []\n",
    "for point in stimulus_profile:\n",
    "    ssp.target_contrast = point * peak_contrast\n",
    "    solutions.append(ssp.linalg_solve())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the modulation\n",
    "_ = ssp.plot_contrast_modulation(solutions)    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6ca18c15-eb37-45c4-b8c1-bb3bbfa008fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plotting the forward projection of contrast for each solution in this case reveals a smooth S-cone modulation with little contrast splatter on the other photoreceptors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5498a363-62bd-48c8-a3dc-7610eeb9c3dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, convert the solutions to settings compatible with the native resolution of the stimulation device."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "c042708c-66b6-4838-a096-306b9320529b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

      "0.000000  2047  2047  2047  2047  2047  2047  2047  2047  2047  2047\n",
      "0.020408  2194  2194  2021  1977  1924  2033  2118  2034  1971  2014\n",
      "0.040816  2338  2339  1995  1907  1804  2019  2189  2020  1897  1982\n",
      "0.061224  2477  2480  1971  1840  1687  2006  2257  2008  1824  1951\n",
      "0.081633  2610  2613  1947  1776  1576  1993  2322  1996  1756  1921\n",
      "...        ...   ...   ...   ...   ...   ...   ...   ...   ...   ...\n",
      "0.918367  1360  1356  2169  2377  2622  2113  1712  2110  2402  2201\n",
      "0.938776  1484  1481  2147  2318  2518  2101  1772  2098  2338  2173\n",
      "0.959184  1617  1614  2123  2254  2407  2088  1837  2086  2270  2143\n",
      "0.979592  1756  1755  2099  2187  2290  2075  1905  2074  2197  2112\n",
      "1.000000  1900  1900  2073  2117  2170  2061  1976  2060  2123  2080\n",
      "\n",
      "[50 rows x 10 columns]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "device_settings = [ssp.w2s(s) for s in solutions]\n",
    "device_settings = pd.DataFrame(device_settings, index=time)\n",
    "device_settings.index.name = 'time'\n",
    "with pd.option_context('display.max_rows', 10):\n",
    "    print(device_settings)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e5cfbf58-a16d-49dc-b6ec-a2ac17ecc260",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now you just need to tell the stimulation device to set the primary inputs to these values at the specified timepoints and it will produce the S-cone modulation shown above. \n",
    "\n",
    "Note that with this method one can also modulate multiple photoreceptors together."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "3f0667ad-f803-49e3-97ac-07d8373842b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 354x354 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ssp.ignore = ['rh']\n",
    "ssp.silence = ['sc', 'mel']\n",
    "ssp.target = ['mc', 'lc']\n",
    "\n",
    "peak_contrast = .2  # Known to be within gamut\n",
    "solutions = []\n",
    "for point in stimulus_profile:\n",
    "    ssp.target_contrast = point * peak_contrast\n",
    "    solutions.append(ssp.linalg_solve())\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Plot the modulation\n",
    "_ = ssp.plot_contrast_modulation(solutions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "790d0ad6-f791-40a9-9468-bd23ac30ff26",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can even modulate photoreceptors in counterphase."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "a048416d-0f09-4a7f-b5c0-fde9039ebce4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 354x354 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ssp.ignore = ['rh']\n",
    "ssp.silence = ['mel']\n",
    "ssp.target = ['sc', 'mc', 'lc']\n",
    "\n",
    "peak_contrast = .35  # Known to be within gamut\n",
    "solutions = []\n",
    "for point in stimulus_profile:\n",
    "    c = point * peak_contrast\n",
    "    ssp.target_contrast = [-c, c, c]\n",
    "    solutions.append(ssp.linalg_solve())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the modulation\n",
    "_ = ssp.plot_contrast_modulation(solutions)"
   ]
  }
